Class DXCAgent

  • java.lang.Object
    • DXCAgent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable

    public class DXCAgent
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Runnable
    The parent class that serves as the base for DXCAgent. It provides common functionality and properties for all agent types.

    • Method Detail

      • start

        public void start()
        Starts the DXCAgent thread. If the thread is not already running, it creates a new thread and starts its execution.

      • CheckforCloudLock

        boolean CheckforCloudLock()
        Checks for the presence of a cloud lock by listing files on the cloud server.
        Returns:
        true if the cloud lock is found, false otherwise.

      • refreshQueue

        public void refreshQueue()

      • saveQueue

        void saveQueue()
        Saves the agent's task queue to the local queue file. The method writes the task details, separated by commas, to the file.

      • sendQueue

        void sendQueue()
        Sends the agent's task queue to the cloud server. The method deletes the old queue on the cloud, uploads the new queue file, and deletes the agent lock file to signal completion. It waits for the cloud lock to be released before proceeding with the upload.

      • readQueue

        void readQueue()
        Reads the agent's task queue from the cloud server. The method uploads the agent lock file and waits for the cloud lock to be released. Once the lock is released, it downloads the queue file from the cloud.

      • releaseQueue

        void releaseQueue()
        Releases the agent's task queue in the cloud server. The method deletes the agent lock file to signal completion and release the queue.

      • run

        public void run()
        Runs the DXCAgent thread. This method is executed when the thread starts running. It processes tasks from the task queue and performs corresponding actions based on the task command. It handles tasks such as downloading, uploading, refreshing, renaming, extracting files, and restarting. The method continuously loops while the state is set to RUNNING.
        Specified by:
        run in interface java.lang.Runnable
        See Also:
        DXCAgent.EXECUTION_STATES, Task

      • stopGracefully

        void stopGracefully()
        Stops the DXCAgent thread gracefully. This method is responsible for gracefully stopping the thread execution. It sets the state to STOPPED, releases the task queue, and outputs the current state.
        See Also:
        DXCAgent.EXECUTION_STATES
